I Read An NYT Infodump. Hundreds of Trackers Followed Me (Unrelated).

A study of a reporter pretending he doesn't waste time on the internet.

By Lily Hoagland

Published September 15, 2019

Farhad Manjoo tracked his online activity for over three hours at work one afternoon and published it in the New York Times, where he works. Farhad Manjoo wants us to believe he only visited 47 sites from 11:56am to 3:15pm.
